HEADWORD: Plebiscitum
<hw>Ple`bis*ci"tum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>plebs</ets>, <ets>plebis</ets>, common people + <ets>scitum</ets>
decree.]</ety> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld> <def>A law enacted by the common
people, under the superintendence of a tribune or some subordinate
plebeian magistrate, without the intervention of the senate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

